25/11/2003
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Prime Minister Zoran Zivkovic's Democratic Party (DS) and its new partners have reached a deal ahead of the 28 December parliamentary elections. Late Monday night (24 November), the DS, the Democratic Centre, the Civil Alliance of Serbia and the Social Democratic Union signed an agreement to run together under the name "DS - Boris Tadic", a reference to the popular federal defence minister who will lead the ticket. Details of the co-operation are to be refined over the next few days. (B92, BBC - 25/11/03)
